Onboarding With A New Client
When you are ready to start working with the new client, schedule a 30-45 min onboarding
session to understand your clients preferences.
Hi Name, I would like to schedule an onboarding call with you to go through your preferences.
Please let me know what works best. Alternatively, if you have a calendar link, I am happy to
schedule through that.
This call will allow me to understand your working style and adapt better. I look forward to it!
Best Your Name
This call should accomplish the following objectives for the assistant:
1. Get to know your client
2. Understands your clients preferences
3. Understand where to look for information
4. Set the stage for your working relationship
During the call, use the preference sheet template to gather as much information as possible.
An Assistants Best Practices Guide

Task: To learn the most effective tips and tricks for working as a remote assistant.
Purpose: The purpose of this guide is to provide assistant-specific guidelines and
recommendations for best practices when interacting with your client. This guide will help
ensure that you provide high-quality and consistent support to your client.
End State: You should be able to have a clear understanding of how to effectively and
professionally interact with your client. This includes understanding how to communicate clearly
and effectively, providing excellent customer service, and troubleshooting problems as needed.
In addition, you will be able to apply the best practices outlined in the guide in your interactions
with clients, resulting in high-quality and consistent support.
Start of Process: This task will start once you get hired by your client.
For a newbie, becoming a remote assistant may sound like an exciting goal. With its flexible
working hours and non-existent commute to work, it's no wonder why people think this is one of
the best jobs around, and this is also why virtual assistants are in demand and increasing in
number.
Here are some best practices to follow when working as a virtual assistant and some real-life
examples:
Understand the basics of a remote assistant job.
Remote assistants are administrative professionals who work from home and provide support to
clients by scheduling appointments, managing email accounts, handling customer inquiries, and
providing general administrative support. To be successful in this role, one must possess strong
organizational and multitasking skills, be comfortable with technology, and be able to quickly
learn new software programs.
Jane is a remote assistant who works from home. She assists several clients in different
industries, including finance, real estate, and e-commerce. She uses various tools to
communicate with her clients, including email, video conferencing, and project management
software. One of her main responsibilities is scheduling appointments for her clients. She uses a
calendar program to keep track of meetings and appointments and sends out reminders to her
clients to ensure they are on time. She also manages several email accounts for her clients,
responding to customer inquiries and forwarding important messages to the relevant parties. In
addition to these tasks, Jane also provides general administrative support. She creates and
updates spreadsheets and documents, organizes files, and performs research as needed. She is
able to multitask effectively and always pays attention to details, ensuring that all tasks are
completed accurately and on time. To excel in her role, Jane continues to stay updated with the
latest technologies and software, learning how to use new programs and tools as needed.
Through her hard work and flexibility, she has built a successful career as a remote assistant.
Develop an environment that makes you productive and successful.
Creating a productive workspace is essential for staying focused and achieving goals. This
includes having a well-lit room, a comfortable chair and desk, and other elements that make the
space conducive to work. Investing in these elements can help to ensure a pleasant and
productive environment.
Jane recognizes the importance of developing an environment that makes her productive and
successful in order to provide the best possible service to her clients. To do this, Jane starts by
decluttering and reorganizing her home office. She ensures that the room has plenty of natural
light by keeping the curtains open during the day and switching on her desk lamp when the sun
goes down. She also invests in a comfortable chair and ergonomic desk that adjusts to her needs;
this allows her to work for hours without feeling discomfort, reducing the risk of pain or strain.
Furthermore, she also makes sure that her office is free of distractions by keeping her phone on
silent and closing unnecessary tabs on her computer. Jane also sets up a schedule for her
workday, which includes time for breaks and exercise, to ensure that she can stay focused and
energized throughout the day. By creating an environment that is conducive to productivity and
success, Jane is able to provide her clients with the high-quality service they expect and deserve
while also taking care of her own well-being.
Maintain professionalism
Maintaining confidentiality and professionalism is an absolute must for any assistant. It is
important to remember to keep your own emotions out of the client-service process and stay
focused on what needs to be done. When things don't go to plan, it is important not to take it
personally. Showing empathy and understanding toward your client's needs is paramount, as well
as recognizing that mistakes can happen. It is your job to work through and resolve any issues
while still maintaining the utmost levels of professionalism and confidentiality.
Jane understands the importance of presenting herself in a professional manner, even though she
does not have a conventional job that requires her to report to a specific place of work and to
dress in accordance with the employer's regulations. She has taken the initiative to find ways to
show her commitment to professionalism, as she recognizes that it is an essential part of a
successful career. For instance, she is careful to adhere to the dress code when attending job
interviews, puts great effort into crafting her resumes and cover letters, and makes sure to be
prompt and courteous when communicating with potential employers. Additionally, she is always
conscious of her online presence and the impression she gives off to employers and is dedicated
to maintaining an up-to-date and polished online profile. Through these measures, Jane is able
to demonstrate her commitment to professionalism and her dedication to her career. Jane is
careful to keep her personal and professional lives separate. She always maintains her business
cards in a different wallet and has never sent a personal email from her work account. She also
ensures that the two worlds are kept distinct by dressing differently when she is at home and
when she is at work. She maintains distinct email addresses for each, and she avoids using social
media such as Facebook to advertise her company. When Jane first meets a prospective client,
she makes it clear that, unless there is an emergency, they should not contact her at home or on
her personal cell phone. Furthermore, she is aware that work and personal matters are two
entirely distinct things and that she should not take business mistakes personally. She never
allows her emotions to enter the matter and always acts professionally. She is mindful of the
difference between personal and professional interactions. She knows that she cannot let her
personal feelings interfere with business decisions and is not afraid, to be honest about her
opinions when necessary.
Maintain confidentiality
Keeping clients' privacy is important in maintaining good relationships with them. Steps to
follow to maintain confidentiality include: avoiding discussing clients, keeping all information
safe and secure, including electronic copies, protecting clients' privacy, and maintaining a
professional reputation.
Jane takes extraordinary measures to ensure the utmost protection of her clients' information.
She believes that it is the responsible thing to do, and it is also an essential part of building a
strong and trusting relationship between her and her clients. She understands that client privacy
is of the utmost importance and goes to great lengths to ensure it is being guarded. Jane is
committed to upholding the highest standards of data security, demonstrating her commitment to
both her clients and her profession. Whenever a friend asks her what she does at her job, she
gives a general overview and refrains from delving into the more sensitive and delicate details.
In addition, in this digital age, Jane makes sure to protect all information, especially financial
data, thoroughly. To ensure security, she uses the most up-to-date encryption software and
passwords, refrains from using public computers or Wi-Fi networks, and forwards any emails
containing sensitive information to her personal account instead of sending it directly. Jane
understands that modern technology can be beneficial but is keenly aware of the potential
dangers it can pose. She is determined to take the necessary steps to ensure that her clients' data
and information remain secure and private at all times. She is diligent in her efforts to protect
her client's confidential information and will not compromise on her commitment to do so. Jane
is devoted to protecting the privacy of her clients and puts their safety and security first.
Good communication is vital for you and your clients.
Effective communication is essential for successful business relationships, especially with
clients. Take time to understand their needs to give professional responses and establish long-
term bonds. Doing so will ensure long-term success. Respectful listening and answers are key to
great client relationships.
We all understand that successful relationships require good communication; otherwise, how
can one engage in business? Jane was aware of this before starting her remote job for a client.
This is especially necessary and essential as remote work does not give the opportunity for face-
to-face meetings. Consequently, keeping in touch regularly and taking the time to provide
updates when tasks are completed or projects are still in progress is vital. Jane is conscious that
this is not only important for her client but also for herself. For instance, if there are sudden
problems at home, it is impossible to just not appear for work and expect your client to
understand. Updating or taking a moment to communicate that you have an emergency is a
major deal. Furthermore, she knows that taking the time to listen and reply respectfully and
appropriately will construct strong relationships, which will be beneficial for everyone. Jane
also understands that when one has a bad day, it is essential not to take it out on the client. Of
course, one may be frustrated or upset with an issue at work but remember that this is not the
fault of the client, and they should not be exposed to it. Jane is a very reliable person, and she
recognizes that this will assist her in the long run. She used to work with people who were not
reliable, but they did not last long in their jobs as they always had excuses for not doing their
job. She does not want to be like them, and she knows that if one is dependable, then one will be
trusted more than those who are not. Jane always makes sure to do her best, and she realizes
that this will contribute to her success.
Make sure expectations are clear from the beginning.
It's important to establish your role as a remote assistant and how you'll be working together with
your client. It's also important that you understand what's expected of you in terms of time
commitment and what is required in terms of skills and expertise. Make sure that you have a
good understanding of how much time each task will take so that you know if it is something that
you will complete or if it needs to be handled by someone else. This will help ensure that no one
gets overloaded with work and that everyone on your team is working effectively together.
A business owner recently hired a remote assistant, Jane, to help manage their social media
marketing efforts. In order to ensure a successful working relationship, the business owner and
Jane held an initial call to discuss their respective roles and expectations. During this call, it
was determined that Jane would be responsible for creating and scheduling posts, responding to
messages, and analyzing the performance of the company's campaigns. Additionally, the
business owner and Jane agreed upon a set number of hours for Jane to work each week and a
specific schedule for when she would be available. Furthermore, they discussed the skills and
experience that the business owner was looking for in Jane, as well as any tasks that needed to
be handled by someone else. By outlining their responsibilities and expectations, the business
owner and Jane were able to ensure that they were both on the same page and had a clear
understanding of their working relationship; this in turn, allowed for a smooth and productive
collaboration.
Be flexible with different types of clients, if possible.
You may find yourself working with clients who have very different needs than you. In some
cases, this can be frustrating. However, it's important to remember that each client is unique and
has other challenges, so be flexible. Also, being flexible can help you be more marketable in the
long run. If your client is looking for a particular type of work that doesn't match your skillset or
expertise, try to find a way to make it work. You should always be prepared to go above and
beyond the call of duty, even when it comes to the most mundane tasks. You will be doing a lot
of work for them, so it pays off financially and emotionally to take whatever time you can from
each client to do as much as possible for them.
Jane, a freelancer, has several clients with different needs. For example, she has a small start-up
client who needs assistance with website design and development, while another client is a large
corporation that primarily needs help with data entry. Jane understands the importance of being
flexible and adapting to different clients and tasks. She puts this into practice and uses the
opportunity to learn and grow in new areas. For the start-up client, she provides a more user-
friendly and visually appealing website design, leading to a continued relationship and a positive
reputation. With the larger corporation, she automates and optimizes the data entry process to
make it more efficient and accurate, resulting in more hours dedicated to the same client. The
effort Jane puts into being flexible, and taking on different tasks, has proven to be beneficial. It
has made her more marketable and opened up new opportunities for her. Her hard work and
dedication are the reasons she has achieved success and continues to do so.
Know Your Niche
It's inevitable that as a remote assistant, you will end up doing most of the things that your clients
ask for, and you should be able to handle everything from customer service to project
management. But you must know what you're good at and aren't good at, so you can focus on
those areas where you excel and improve on the things you arent good at. For example, if you
are an expert in Canva, then make sure that's the most useful tool for your client. If not, try
something else.
Jane is a remote assistant that specializes in graphic design. She has a lot of experience and
skills in using Canva, a graphic design software. She also has some skills in other graphic design
software, but she's more proficient with Canva. She also has some knowledge of project
management but is not a professional. She has a client that needs help with designing marketing
materials and some project management tasks. Jane starts by analyzing the client's needs and
what they want to achieve with their marketing materials. She presents her expertise in Canva
and offers the client a portfolio of her previous work done with the software. The client is
satisfied with Janes skills and decides to hire her. During the project, Jane makes sure that the
client's design needs are met. Also, she provides suggestions and advice on design aspects that
could make the materials more effective. On the project management side, Jane focused on the
tasks that she is proficient in. When she encountered tasks that she was not comfortable or not
good at, she communicated with the client and informed them that he will be outsourcing those
tasks to someone else that specializes in that field. This approach enabled Jane to deliver high-
quality work, meet the client's needs, and at the same time, build trust and relationships with her
client. In this way, by knowing her niche and focusing on areas where she excels, Jane is able to
provide high-quality services to her clients and maintain a positive working relationship with
them.
Take the initiative to suggest ideas and solutions when needed
It's essential to be proactive and take the initiative when needed in the workplace. Whether
you're tackling a problem or have a great idea to improve the workplace, speaking up and sharing
your thoughts is always beneficial. Of course, proposing ideas and solutions can sometimes be
met with opposition. But if you're confident in your idea and present it in a positive way, you're
more likely to convince others of its value. Also, it's important to remember that even if your
suggestion is immediately rejected, it can still be given a serious thought. By taking the initiative
and offering ideas, you show that you're committed to finding ways to make the workplace more
efficient.
